{"word":"ἀδίκημα","slug":"ἀδίκημα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀδίκημα</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀδικέω'><el>ἀδικέω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a wrong done, a wrong</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>injuria</el>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>a wrong done to one</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>that which is got by wrong, ill-gotten goods</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}